The decomposing body of a young man has been found in his room at Feyinfolu street, behind Delight Hotel in Ado Ekiti, the state capital.
The death of the Federal Polytechnic, Ado Ekiti undergraduate had remain a mystery as no one could ascertain how he died.
Even his neighbours and landlord could not give any reasonable information about his death.





According to information gathered by pressmen, his mother who lived in Ise-Ekiti came to visit him after she called his lines many times without response, only to find her son on the floor in pool of blood but with a scary appearance.
His body and eye balls had swollen while his flesh were peeling.
Many residents suspected that he might have been attacked by ghosts while engaging in money rituals.
This is because the two phones recovered with other valuables in the room appeared too expensive and luxurious for an undergraduate of his status.
As at the time of this report, the remains of the deceased had been evacuated by concerned authorities.



